  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior/Property Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Collaborate with team members to coordinate and oversee contractors in the execution and maintenance of daily estate, horticultural, and cyclical improvement works at public housing estates.</p></li><li><p>Conduct regular site inspections, supervise contractors’ performance, identify defects, and ensure timely rectification of issues.</p></li><li><p>Manage and respond to residents' feedback, including providing follow-up and call-back services after defect resolution.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with grassroots leaders to discuss estate maintenance matters and ensure timely follow-up on related issues.</p></li><li><p>Support grassroots leaders in the planning and execution of community events and activities.</p></li><li><p>Attend house visits, grassroots meetings, and upgrading project discussions, including those scheduled after office hours, when required.</p></li><li><p>Respond promptly to urgent cases referred by managers, grassroots leaders, or the EMSU.</p></li><li><p>Address residents’ feedback and service requests, and assist in managing arrears cases.</p></li><li><p>Perform administrative tasks such as sourcing quotations, issuing work orders, and preparing applications for relevant funding.</p></li><li><p>Undertake any other ad-hoc duties as assigned by management.</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>ITE/Diploma Holders</p></li><li><p>Minimum 2 years in similar role</p></li><li><p>A team player with good interpersonal and organization skills</p></li><li><p>People-oriented with a willingness to learn</p></li><li><p>Able to work under pressure</p></li></ul>",
